#: examples/catalog.py:153
msgid "[Soft hyphens and no-break spaces]"
msgstr "Soft hyphens and no-break spaces"

#: examples/catalog.py:155
msgid ""
"[A justified column set twice: the long words breaking at their soft hyphens "
"with a hyphen shown, or left whole, and a figure a no-break space keeps "
"together.]"
msgstr ""
"A justified column set twice: the long words breaking at their soft hyphens "
"with a hyphen shown, or left whole, and a figure a no-break space keeps "
"together."

#: examples/catalog.py:166
msgid "[Break points after a slash or a hyphen]"
msgstr "Break points after a slash or a hyphen"

#: examples/catalog.py:168
msgid ""
"[A justified column set twice: file paths and compounds running past the "
"edge with no break points, then wrapping where a break after a slash or a "
"hyphen is allowed.]"
msgstr ""
"A justified column set twice: file paths and compounds running past the edge "
"with no break points, then wrapping where a break after a slash or a hyphen "
"is allowed."

#: examples/catalog.py:179
msgid "[Clipping paths]"
msgstr "Clipping paths"

#: examples/catalog.py:181
msgid ""
"[A field of stripes shown through two clipping paths: a disc set by the "
"nonzero rule, and a frame set by the even-odd rule over two nested "
"rectangles.]"
msgstr ""
"A field of stripes shown through two clipping paths: a disc set by the "
"nonzero rule, and a frame set by the even-odd rule over two nested "
"rectangles."

#: examples/catalog.py:192
msgid "[Grey, screen and printing colours]"
msgstr "Grey, screen and printing colours"

#: examples/catalog.py:194
msgid ""
"[Swatches in each of the three colour spaces — a grey as one number, a "
"screen colour as three, a printing colour as four inks — each captioned with "
"the operators it wrote, and one mid-grey said three ways.]"
msgstr ""
"Swatches in each of the three colour spaces — a grey as one number, a screen "
"colour as three, a printing colour as four inks — each captioned with the "
"operators it wrote, and one mid-grey said three ways."

#: examples/catalog.py:206
msgid "[Colour the document defines]"
msgstr "Colour the document defines"

#: examples/catalog.py:208
msgid ""
"[The same six colours said as bare numbers and then through the sRGB profile "
"the file carries, plus a lightness ramp and a hue sweep in CIE L*a*b*: "
"colour that still means the same thing on another screen and on a press.]"
msgstr ""
"The same six colours said as bare numbers and then through the sRGB profile "
"the file carries, plus a lightness ramp and a hue sweep in CIE L*a*b*: "
"colour that still means the same thing on another screen and on a press."

#: examples/catalog.py:220
msgid "[Inks on plates of their own]"
msgstr "Inks on plates of their own"

#: examples/catalog.py:222
msgid ""
"[Two inks the press carries on plates of their own, each at ten tints, a "
"piece of work set in both, and the crosshairs that line the plates up — set "
"in the colorant every plate answers to.]"
msgstr ""
"Two inks the press carries on plates of their own, each at ten tints, a "
"piece of work set in both, and the crosshairs that line the plates up — set "
"in the colorant every plate answers to."

#: examples/catalog.py:233
msgid "[Transparency and blend modes]"
msgstr "Transparency and blend modes"

#: examples/catalog.py:235
msgid ""
"[Half-opacity fills that overlap and mix, and one orange square laid over a "
"blue bar in four blend modes, through an extended graphics state.]"
msgstr ""
"Half-opacity fills that overlap and mix, and one orange square laid over a "
"blue bar in four blend modes, through an extended graphics state."

#: examples/catalog.py:246
msgid "[Axial and radial gradients]"
msgstr "Axial and radial gradients"

#: examples/catalog.py:248
msgid ""
"[Axial and radial gradients painted into clipped boxes: a horizontal and a "
"diagonal two-colour blend, a radial one whose outer colour is extended to "
"the corners, and a three-stop blend from a stitched function.]"
msgstr ""
"Axial and radial gradients painted into clipped boxes: a horizontal and a "
"diagonal two-colour blend, a radial one whose outer colour is extended to "
"the corners, and a three-stop blend from a stitched function."

#: examples/catalog.py:260
msgid "[Text and shapes filled with a gradient]"
msgstr "Text and shapes filled with a gradient"

#: examples/catalog.py:262
msgid ""
"[A gradient as the colour something is filled with, through a shading "
"pattern: a headline whose letters are windows onto a three-stop blend, and a "
"panel filled with a radial one.]"
msgstr ""
"A gradient as the colour something is filled with, through a shading "
"pattern: a headline whose letters are windows onto a three-stop blend, and a "
"panel filled with a radial one."

#: examples/catalog.py:273
msgid "[Content shown and hidden by layer]"
msgstr "Content shown and hidden by layer"

#: examples/catalog.py:275
msgid ""
"[One floor plan on four layers a reader shows and hides: the furniture and "
"the dimensions shown, the notes hidden until asked for, and a draft mark "
"that is looked at but never printed.]"
msgstr ""
"One floor plan on four layers a reader shows and hides: the furniture and "
"the dimensions shown, the notes hidden until asked for, and a draft mark "
"that is looked at but never printed."

#: examples/catalog.py:286
msgid "[One drawing, placed many times]"
msgstr "One drawing, placed many times"

#: examples/catalog.py:288
msgid ""
"[One badge built as a drawing and placed eight times, plus once at half "
"size: the file holds its operators once, whatever it costs to place.]"
msgstr ""
"One badge built as a drawing and placed eight times, plus once at half size: "
"the file holds its operators once, whatever it costs to place."

#: examples/catalog.py:299
msgid "[One cell, tiled across whatever it fills]"
msgstr "One cell, tiled across whatever it fills"

#: examples/catalog.py:301
msgid ""
"[Six panels filled with tiling patterns — bars, dots, a slant from the "
"pattern's matrix, brickwork, two patterns crossing, a wider step — and a "
"wordmark whose letters are windows onto the brickwork.]"
msgstr ""
"Six panels filled with tiling patterns — bars, dots, a slant from the "
"pattern's matrix, brickwork, two patterns crossing, a wider step — and a "
"wordmark whose letters are windows onto the brickwork."

#: examples/catalog.py:313
msgid "[One rectangle, four masks]"
msgstr "One rectangle, four masks"

#: examples/catalog.py:315
msgid ""
"[The same flat rectangle four times over, each under a different soft mask — "
"a gradient fade, a radial vignette, letters cut through it, a coverage read "
"from opacity — and a band that runs out with a tag painted whole inside it.]"
msgstr ""
"The same flat rectangle four times over, each under a different soft mask — "
"a gradient fade, a radial vignette, letters cut through it, a coverage read "
"from opacity — and a band that runs out with a tag painted whole inside it."

#: examples/catalog.py:327
msgid "[Text poured into columns]"
msgstr "Text poured into columns"

#: examples/catalog.py:329
msgid ""
"[One long passage poured into three columns, each fitting the lines its "
"height allows and handing the rest to the next.]"
msgstr ""
"One long passage poured into three columns, each fitting the lines its "
"height allows and handing the rest to the next."

#: examples/catalog.py:339
msgid "[Paragraph indents and spacing]"
msgstr "Paragraph indents and spacing"

#: examples/catalog.py:341
